This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it deals with a consensus protocol that requires communication between multiple nodes. It could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as Byzantine fault tolerance is a common topic in cryptography. Additionally, the paper could be categorized under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as consensus protocols involve data structures and algorithms. The Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is also a possibility as consensus protocols are used in distributed control systems. Lastly, the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is a less likely possibility as machine learning algorithms can also benefit from consensus protocols.
